Our God, our ancientsò God, may our prayer arise and come to
you, and be beheld, and be acceptable. Let it be heard, acted
upon, remembered--the memory of us and all our needs, the
memory of our ancestors, the memory of messianic hopes, the
memory of Jerusalem your holy city, and the memory of all your
kin, the house of Israel, all surviving in your presence. Act for
goodness and grace, for love and care; for life, well-being and
peace, on this day of/PR

/PR

/ITOn Pesah/±:/XX the festival of matzot./PR

/ITOn Shavuot:/XX the festival of shavuot./PR

/ITOn Sukkot:/XX the festival of sukkot./PR

/ITOn Shemini Atzeret / Simh/±at Torah:/XX the eighth day of festivity./PR

/PR

Remember us this day, /SCA/XXLL-/XXK/XXNOWING /XXO/XXNE/XX, our God, for
goodness. Favor us this day with blessing. Preserve us this day
for life. With your redeeming nurturing word, be kind and
generous. Act tenderly on our behalf, and grant us victory over
all our trials. Truly, our eyes turn toward you, for you are a
providing God; gracious and merciful are you./PR

/PR

Our God, our ancientsò God;/PR

May it be your will that a heavenly inspiration/PR

be awakened in us on this holy day/PR

to rebuild the Land of Israel,/PR

to renew it and to make it holy for your service,/PR

and may peace prevail there/PR

as well as freedom, justice, and the rule of Law,/PR

as it is written by your prophet:/PR

"Truly, Torah shall go forth from Zion,/PR

and the word of the /SCE/XXTERNAL/XX from Jerusalem!"/PR

And it is said: "Let none do harm,/PR

let none destroy, throughout my holy mountain,/PR

for the earth is filled with knowledge of the /SCO/XXMNIPRESENT/XX,/PR

as the waters fill the sea."/PI/PR

